The Kitui health department yesterday sent an alert over possible cholera and diarrhea outbreak following heavy rains currently experienced in the county. Director of health Dr. Allan Owino in a letter said chorela outbreak across the country had already affected more than 20,000 people in 31 counties including neighbouring counties of Makueni, Machakos, Tana River, and Garissa over the last three years. “Children are at the most significant risk as they have weaker immune systems,” he said.